Phonion: a secure voip and messaging device
===========================================

Dependendencies:
================
    Install on Raspberry Pi::
    * # Install Qt deps
    * sudo apt-get install libdbus1-dev
    *./configure -release -opengl es2 -dbus -lrt -lpthread
                 -optimized-qmake -no-pch
                 -make libs -make tools -reduce-exports -sysroot /mnt/rasp-pi-rootfs
                 -device linux-rasp-pi-g++
                 -device-option CROSS_COMPILE=/home/christopher/workspace/rpi/tools/arm-bcm2708/gcc-linaro-arm-linux-gnueabihf-raspbian/bin/arm-linux-gnueabihf-
                 -prefix /usr/local/qt5pi/ -opensource -confirm-license -qt-xcb

    * # Install Tortalk deps
    * sudo apt-get install libboost-python

    * # Install Mumble deps
    * sudo apt-get install build-essential pkg-config qt4-dev-tools libqt4-dev libspeex1 \
                libspeex-dev libboost-dev libasound2-dev libssl-dev g++ \
                libspeechd-dev libzeroc-ice-dev ice-slice libpulse-dev slice2cpp \
                libcap-dev libspeexdsp-dev libprotobuf-dev protobuf-compiler \
                libogg-dev libavahi-compat-libdnssd-dev libsndfile1-dev \
                libg15daemon-client-dev libxi-dev libopus-dev

Building:
=========

Cross-Compiling:
================
    * Use http://www.ics.com/blog/building-qt-5-raspberry-pi#.UtFeKZCldhE to setup
      a toolchain and cross compile Qt5.
    * Setup a base raspbian image with all dependencies as a loopback device.
    * /usr/local/qt5pi/bin/qmake && make
    * # Rsync to the pi.
    * rsync -av -e ssh phonion/ pi@<PI_IP_ADDR>:phonion

Security Concerns:
==================
    * Mumble using OpenSSL v1.0. This should be restricted to at least v2.0 if not v3.0.
    * Buffer attacks in messaging. Set hard limit on characters.
